		  <para>You have the volume (V) and the mass (m). You need the number of moles (n) and the molar mass (M).</para>
		  <para>M(<chem_compound>HCl</chem_compound>) = <number>1.01</number> + <number>35.45</number> = <unit_number><number>36.46</number><unit>g.mol<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number>.</para>
		  <para>m(<chem_compound>HCl</chem_compound>) = <unit_number><number>32.8</number><unit>mg</unit></unit_number> <latex>\times \dfrac{<number>0.001</number> {\text{ g}}}{<number>1</number> {\text{ mg}}}</latex> = <unit_number><number>0.0328</number><unit>g</unit></unit_number></para>
