		<para><emphasis effect="bold">Acid + metal</emphasis> <latex>\to</latex> <emphasis effect="bold">salt + hydrogen</emphasis></para>
		<para>A dilute acid is added to a pure metal to form a salt and hydrogen gas. The salt is formed by the metal cation and the anion from the acid. In this reaction the metal is acting as a base. For example:</para>
