		<title>What are the reactants?</title>
		<para>An acid (<chem_compound>H_{2}SO_{4}</chem_compound>) and a base (<chem_compound>NH_{3}</chem_compound>).</para>
	      </workstep>
	      <workstep>
		<title>What will the products be?</title>
		<para>As this is the reaction of an acid and a base (with no hydroxide anion), there will be a salt as a product. There may or may not be another product.</para>
		<para>sulfuric acid + ammonia <latex>\to</latex> salt (+ maybe another product)</para>
	      </workstep>
	      <workstep>
		<title>What is the formula of the salt?</title>
		<para>The cation will come from the base (<chem_compound>NH_{4}^{+}</chem_compound>). The anion will come from the acid (<chem_compound>SO_{4}^{2-}</chem_compound>). Due to the charges on the cation and anion there must be two <chem_compound>NH_{4}^{+}</chem_compound> for every one <chem_compound>SO_{4}^{2-}</chem_compound>.</para>
