    <section type="subsection">
      <title><latex>K_{w}</latex></title>
      <shortcode>Shortcode</shortcode>
      <para>Water ionises to a very small extent:</para>
      <para><chem_compound>H_{2}O(ℓ) + H_{2}O(ℓ)</chem_compound> <latex>\rightleftharpoons</latex> <chem_compound>H_{3}O^{+}(aq) + OH^{-}(aq)</chem_compound></para>
      <para>This type of reaction (the transfer of a proton between identical molecules) is known as <emphasis effect="bold">auto-protolysis</emphasis>. This reaction is also known as the <emphasis effect="bold">auto-ionisation</emphasis> of water and the ions formed are a conjugate acid and base pair of water:</para>
      <pspicture>
	<code>
