	    </item>
	  </list>
	</section>
	  <section>
	    <title>Method</title>
	    <note type="warning">
	      <para>Concentrated acids and bases can cause serious burns. We suggest using gloves and safety glasses whenever you work with an acid or a base. Handle all chemicals with care.</para>
	    </note>
	    <list list-type="enumerated">
	      <item>
		<para>Prepare a standard solution using <unit_number><number>11.00</number><unit>g</unit></unit_number> of oxalic acid in the <unit_number><number>250</number><unit>cm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number> volumetric flask (remember to follow the method from the formal <emphasis effect="italics">preparation of a standard solution</emphasis> experiment).</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>Label one of the beakers <emphasis effect="italics"><chem_compound>NaOH</chem_compound></emphasis>. Use a measuring cylinder to measure approximately <unit_number><number>100</number><unit>cm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number> of water into the beaker. Add approximately <unit_number><number>4</number><unit>g</unit></unit_number> of <chem_compound>NaOH</chem_compound> to the beaker and stir.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>Label a conical flask <emphasis effect="bold">1</emphasis> and transfer <unit_number><number>20</number><unit>cm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number> of the sodium hydroxide to the conical flask.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>Add a few drops of the phenolphthalein indicator to conical flask 1.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>Measure <unit_number><number>10</number><unit>cm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number> of the oxalic acid solution in the second measuring cylinder.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>Pour the <unit_number><number>10</number><unit>cm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number> oxalic acid solution into conical flask 1. Swirl the flask.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>If there is no colour change measure <unit_number><number>5</number><unit>cm<sup>3</sup></unit></unit_number> oxalic acid in the measuring cylinder and add this to conical flask 1. Swirl the flask.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
		<para>Repeat step <number>7</number> until the colour change remains after swirling. Calculate the volume of oxalic acid solution added. This is your <emphasis effect="italics">rough titration</emphasis>.</para>
	      </item>
	      <item>
