      </pspicture>
      <caption>
	<para>Guanidine (left) and guanidine hydroxide (right). Guanidine hydroxide is formed from guanidine carbonate and calcium hydroxide.</para>
      </caption>
    </figure>
    <para>Some comparisons between lye and no-lye hair relaxers are given in Table <link target-id="tab:acidsandbases:hairrelaxers"/>.</para>
