	  <entry>
	    <problem>
	      <para>During the baking process, baking soda reacts with an acid (e.g. acetic acid in vinegar) to produce carbon dioxide and water, as shown by the reaction equation below:</para>
	      <para><chem_compound>NaHCO_{3}(aq) + CH_{3}COOH(aq)</chem_compound> <latex>\to</latex> <chem_compound>CH_{3}COONa(aq) + CO_{2}(g) + H_{2}O(ℓ)</chem_compound></para>
	      <para>Use the above equation to explain why the cake rises during this baking process.</para>
