	  <para>From the balanced equation we see that the molar ratio of <chem_compound>NaHCO_{3}</chem_compound> to <chem_compound>HCl</chem_compound> is <number>1</number>:<number>1</number>.</para>
	  <para>Therefore, n(<chem_compound>HCl</chem_compound>) = n(<chem_compound>NaHCO_{3}</chem_compound>) = <unit_number><number>0.26</number><unit>mol</unit></unit_number></para>
	  <para><latex>\text{C} = \dfrac{\text{n}}{\text{V}}</latex> therefore <latex>\text{V} = \dfrac{\text{n}}{\text{C}}</latex></para>
